data.name: TreeDataModelEvent
desc: An event used by a XTreeDataModel to notify changes in the data model to the XTreeControl.
You usually need to fill this event only if you implement the XTreeDataModel yourself.

items.name: Nodes
lines: contains the changed, added or removed nodes.
All nodes must have ParentNode as parent.

items.name: ParentNode
lines: holds the parent node for changed, added or removed nodes.
If this is null, Nodes must contain only the root node
